short_description:
This project is an umbrella project for a few subprojects whose aim is to improve the usability of the CLOS MOP across different Common Lisp implementations. It provides:
* a test suite to check which CLOS MOP features are and are not supported in a specific Common Lisp implementation;
* Closer to MOP, a compatibility library that adds missing features and/or replaces existing features with versions that better reflect the CLOS MOP specification in AMOP
* ContextL, a CLOS extension for Context-oriented Programming implemented on top of Closer to MOP;
* Filtered Functions, a CLOS extension for generic function invocation on top of Closer to MOP that effectively provides a variant of predicate dispatch.

ContextL and Filtered Functions are useful libraries in their own right, but also make extensive use of the CLOS MOP.
